      • buildStrokes

        public void buildStrokes(Set<String> attributeNames,
                         double deviatAngle,
                         double deviatSum,
                         boolean noStop)

        Build the 'Strokes' of a network. Strokes are groups of network segments that follow the perceptual grouping principle of Good Continuity (Gestalt).

        Parameters:
        attributeNames - : the set of attribute names used for attribute continuity.
        deviatAngle - : the limit incident angle for continuity
        deviatSum - : the limit sum incident angle differences between consecutive pts.
        noStop - : true if the stroke always has to continue when there is a unique follower.
